column8:
Suleiman , or Kanuni Sultan Suleyman also known as Suleiman The Magnificent. He was the tenth and longest-reigning Sultan of the Ottoman Empire, from 1520 to his death in 1566.

Known for his long reign, changes he made to Law, education & taxation and his numerous conquests across Europe.
